# BMS Automation Framework

## Overview

This repository contains a **Playwright-based UI automation framework** designed for scalability, maintainability, and CI execution. The framework follows clear separation of concerns (Pages, Fixtures, Services, Utils, Tests) and supports role-based functional testing with Allure reporting and CI integration.

The structure is intentionally simple but production-ready, suitable for both team collaboration and interview demonstrations.

---

## Tech Stack

* **Playwright** (UI & API Automation)
* **JavaScript** (Tests, Pages, Fixtures, Services)
* **TypeScript** (Playwright configuration)
* **MongoDB** (Database testing & data setup)
* **Allure** (Test Reporting)
* **Node.js / npm**
* **Jenkins / GitHub Actions** (CI-ready)

---

## Project Structure

```
BMS_AUTOMATION
│
├── fixtures/
│   └── auth.fixture.js        # Authentication & logged-in state fixtures
│
├── pages/
│   ├── login.page.js          # Login page object
│   ├── register.page.js       # Registration page object
│   ├── admin-home.page.js     # Admin home/dashboard page object
│   ├── partner-home.page.js   # Partner home/dashboard page object
│   ├── user-home.page.js      # User home/dashboard page object
│   ├── user-profile.page.js   # User profile page object
│   ├── movie-modal.page.js    # Movie modal page object
│   ├── show-booking.page.js   # Show booking page object
│   ├── theatre-modal.page.js  # Theatre modal page object
│   ├── stripe-checkout-frame.page.js # Stripe payment integration
│   └── [other page objects]   # Additional page objects for various UI components
│
├── services/
│   ├── auth.service.js        # Authentication service
│   ├── mongo.service.js       # MongoDB database interaction utilities
│   └── show.service.js        # Show management service
│
├── utils/
│   └── time.util.js           # Stateless helper utilities (date/time, formatting)
│
├── test-data/
│   ├── user.json              # User test data
│   ├── movie.json             # Movie test data
│   └── show.json              # Show test data
│
├── tests/
│   ├── ui/
│   │   ├── ui-functional/     # Functional test cases by role
│   │   │   ├── admin/         # Admin role test cases
│   │   │   ├── partner/       # Partner role test cases
│   │   │   ├── common/        # Common test utilities and shared tests
│   │   │   └── user/          # User role test cases
│   │   │       └── user-home.spec.js  # User home flow tests
│   │   └── ui-e2e/            # End-to-end test scenarios
│   │       ├── admin-adding-movie.spec.js   # Admin movie creation flow
│   │       ├── partner-adding-show.spec.js  # Partner show addition flow
│   │       └── user-booking-show.spec.js    # User show booking flow
│   └── api/
│       └── user.api.spec.js   # API test cases for user endpoints
│
├── playwright.config.ts       # Playwright configuration
├── Jenkinsfile                # CI pipeline definition
├── package.json               # Project dependencies and scripts
└── .env                       # Environment variables (not committed)
```

---

## Architecture Principles

### 1. Page Object Model (POM)

* All UI locators and actions are encapsulated inside `*.page.js` files
* Tests never directly interact with selectors
* Improves maintainability when UI changes

### 2. Fixtures for State Management

* `auth.fixture.js` is responsible for authentication-related setup
* Fixtures provide **ready-to-use state** (e.g., logged-in user)
* Avoids repetitive login steps inside tests

### 3. Services Layer

* `services/` contains backend, API, or database interactions
* Keeps non-UI logic out of tests and pages
* Enables hybrid API + UI testing

### 4. Utilities Layer

* `utils/` contains pure, stateless helper functions
* No Playwright or test logic allowed here

### 5. Test Organization Strategy

**Functional Tests** - Organized by business roles:
* `admin` - Admin-specific workflows
* `partner` - Partner-specific workflows  
* `user` - User-specific workflows
* `common` - Shared/common test utilities

Role-based organization makes ownership, execution, and scaling easier.

**E2E Tests** - Complete end-to-end user journeys
* `admin-adding-movie.spec.js` - Admin movie creation flow
* `partner-adding-show.spec.js` - Partner show addition flow
* `user-booking-show.spec.js` - User show booking flow

**API Tests** - Backend API testing
* Located in `tests/api/`
* Covers API endpoints and business logic validation

---

## Test Naming Conventions

| File Type   | Convention    | Example             |
| ----------- | ------------- | ------------------- |
| Test        | `.spec.js`    | `user-home.spec.js` |
| Page Object | `.page.js`    | `user-home.page.js` |
| Fixture     | `.fixture.js` | `auth.fixture.js`   |
| Service     | `.service.js` | `mongo.service.js`  |
| Utility     | `.util.js`    | `time.util.js`      |

---

## Running Tests

### Install dependencies

```bash
npm install
```

### Run all tests

```bash
npx playwright test
```

### Run UI tests only

```bash
npx playwright test tests/ui
```

### Run functional tests only

```bash
npx playwright test tests/ui/ui-functional
```

### Run E2E tests only

```bash
npx playwright test tests/ui/ui-e2e
```

### Run API tests only

```bash
npx playwright test tests/api
```

### Run tests for a specific role

```bash
npx playwright test tests/ui/ui-functional/admin
npx playwright test tests/ui/ui-functional/partner
npx playwright test tests/ui/ui-functional/user
```

### Run a specific test

```bash
npx playwright test tests/ui/ui-functional/user/user-home.spec.js
```

### Run tests in headed mode

```bash
npx playwright test --headed
```

---

## Reports

### Playwright HTML Report

After execution:

```bash
npx playwright show-report
```

### Allure Report

```bash
allure generate allure-results --clean
allure open
```

> In CI, Allure reports are generated automatically.

---

## CI Integration

* `Jenkinsfile` defines the pipeline steps
* Supports headless execution
* Generates Playwright + Allure reports
* Suitable for GitHub Actions or Jenkins

---

## Environment Configuration

Environment variables are managed using `.env`:

```
BASE_URL=
USERNAME=
PASSWORD=
```

> `.env` is excluded from version control.

---

## Design Goals

* Clear separation of concerns
* Minimal abstraction, maximum readability
* Scalable for teams and CI
* Easy onboarding for new contributors

---

